        "rich_text_ccxpK9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Wondering how much does a diamond ring cost in India? The answer isn't a single number it's a blend of factors from diamond quality to metal choice. At Lucira Jewelry, we believe in radical transparency, helping you understand every element that contributes to the final price. This guide will demystify the costs and show you how to find a stunning, ethically sourced lab-grown diamond ring that fits your budget and style perfectly.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kKqW7n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Understanding the Key Factors That Determine Diamond ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Understanding the Key Factors That Determine Diamond </h2>",
            "custom_id": "radiant"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_yYFrht": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Ring Prices in India",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Ring Prices in India</h3><p>The final price tag of a diamond ring is determined by a combination of characteristics, famously known as the 4Cs. Understanding these is the first step in figuring out how much a diamond ring costs in India for your specific needs. Lucira Jewelry ensures every diamond is graded on these principles, giving you complete clarity on your purchase.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BxFmqg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Impact of Carat Weight on Overall Cost",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Impact of Carat Weight on Overall Cost</h2>",
            "custom_id": "the-impact"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_AynJ8F": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/2_4eeb2d8a-aaae-4327-a64d-c9f95bbd72f7.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Many people think carat is about size, but it's actually a unit of weight (1 carat = 200 milligrams). While a higher carat weight generally means a larger-looking diamond, the price doesn't just climb it leaps. A 2-carat diamond will cost significantly more than double the price of a 1-carat diamond of similar quality. This is where Lucira's lab-grown diamonds offer a distinct advantage.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Vt7GJ4": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Impact of Carat Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Exponential Pricing: Price increases exponentially as carat weight goes up because larger diamonds are rarer.<br/><br/> The Lucira Advantage: Our lab-grown diamonds make larger carat weights more accessible and affordable, allowing you to get a more impressive stone without compromising your budget.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jbd43L": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Clarity, Color, and Cut are Crucial for a Diamond's Value",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Clarity, Color, and Cut are Crucial for a Diamond's Value</h2><p>Beyond weight, these three 'Cs' define a diamond's beauty and brilliance, heavily influencing its value.</p>",
            "custom_id": "Why"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_PYNpgj": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Clarity, Color Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<ul><li>Clarity: Measures the absence of internal inclusions or external blemishes. A flawless diamond is rare and highly-priced.<br/><br/></li><li>Color: Refers to the lack of color in a diamond. The scale runs from D (colorless) to Z (light yellow), with colorless diamonds being the most valuable.<br/><br/></li><li>Cut: This is arguably the most important 'C' as it dictates how well a diamond reflects light. A superior cut can make a diamond appear larger and more brilliant. Lucira Jewelry prioritizes exceptional cuts to maximize the sparkle of every lab-grown diamond, ensuring you receive a stone with breathtaking fire and life.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ejh96n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Lucira Advantage: Lab-Grown Diamonds and ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Lucira Advantage: Lab-Grown Diamonds and </h2>",
            "custom_id": "the-lucira"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BWVmEe": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Transparent Pricing",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Transparent Pricing</h3>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bPLMNC": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Transparent Pricing Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>A key factor in determining how much a diamond ring costs in India is the origin of the diamond itself. Lucira Jewelry champions lab-grown diamonds, which are physically, chemically, and optically identical to their mined counterparts but offer remarkable value and ethical peace of mind.</p>",
            "custom_id": "classic"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_TbC4mN": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What is the Original Diamond Ring Price for Lab-Grown Stones?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What is the Original Diamond Ring Price for Lab-Grown Stones?</h2><p>When considering the Original Diamond Ring price, lab-grown diamonds present a compelling financial advantage. They typically cost 30–50% less than mined diamonds of the same size and quality. This isn't because they are 'fake' they are real diamonds created in a controlled environment. This significant price difference means you can afford a larger or higher-quality diamond for your budget when you choose Lucira. The lower Original Diamond Ring price for lab-grown stones is purely due to a more efficient and sustainable supply chain.</p>",
            "custom_id": "what-is"
          }
        },
